parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Rear Brake Light Wiring and Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake light due to faulty wiring can cause intermittent or complete loss of brake light function, reducing the ability to warn other motorists of the driver's intentions, which can lead to accidents or crashes without warning.
symptoms: Rear brake light failure
passenger tail light failure
warning messages appear on the dashboard
brake light
turn signal
and/or reverse lamp functions stop working
intermittent light operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission case failure can cause a leak of transmission fluid, leading to malfunction or failure of the transmission, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leak
loss of transmission fluid
transmission malfunction
transmission failure
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become twisted, jammed, or stuck in the B-pillar, rendering it non-functional and increasing the risk of injury or accident in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The driver's side seatbelt is slow to retract
gets twisted when retracting
requires manual assistance to feed the belt into the B-pillar
becomes jammed or stuck in the B-pillar
requires excessive strength and effort to pull it back out
and may become non-functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong odor of fuel inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leaks
decreased fuel efficiency
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unprovoked shattering of the sunroof can cause a hazardous situation, potentially leading to injuries from flying glass shards, distractions while driving, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes or shatters without any apparent reason
glass shards fall into the vehicle
and pieces of glass may fly off the car and hit other vehicles or pedestrians.
